{"questionId":"4202","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An X-ray beam of intensity <em>I</em><sub>0</sub> is incident on lead. After travelling a distance <em>x</em> through the&nbsp;lead the intensity of the beam is reduced to <em>I</em>.</p>\n<p>The graph shows the variation of ln<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{I}{{{I_0}}}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>I</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>I</mi>\n              <mn>0</mn>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> with <em>x.</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/51fbb1e61a936a8514f82b8493a223e472f88f72.png\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that the attenuation coefficient of lead is 60 cm<sup>–1</sup>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>evidence of finding the gradient</p>\n<p><em>μ</em> =&nbsp;«– gradient =» 59.9 «cm<sup>–1</sup>»</p>","meta":{"questionId":"4202","referenceCode":"17N.3.HL.TZ0.16a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that the attenuation coefficient of lead is 60 cm–1.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Additional higher level option topics)","C.4 – Medical imaging (HL only)","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Additional higher level option topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}